      <h1 id="randomization-homework">Randomization Homework</h1>

<p>In these short examples, I’ll show how I would solve this week’s homework using vectors.</p>

<p><a href="http://assets.runemadsen.com/pintori5-60c69425c0d5220d0fe4e6eace9fd53a_large.jpg"><img src="http://assets.runemadsen.com/pintori5-60c69425c0d5220d0fe4e6eace9fd53a_medium.jpg" srcset="http://assets.runemadsen.com/pintori5-60c69425c0d5220d0fe4e6eace9fd53a_medium.jpg 800w, http://assets.runemadsen.com/pintori5-60c69425c0d5220d0fe4e6eace9fd53a_large.jpg 1440w" sizes="600px" /></a></p>

<p>Here’s the most basic sketch, in black and white, that demonstrates how to use vectors and perlin noise to calculate the positions of the triangles.</p>

<p><a href="http://assets.runemadsen.com/randomization_simplest-018dfa415f3db6b8404e43e67a1c9e37_large.png"><img src="http://assets.runemadsen.com/randomization_simplest-018dfa415f3db6b8404e43e67a1c9e37_medium.png" srcset="http://assets.runemadsen.com/randomization_simplest-018dfa415f3db6b8404e43e67a1c9e37_medium.png 800w, http://assets.runemadsen.com/randomization_simplest-018dfa415f3db6b8404e43e67a1c9e37_large.png 1440w" sizes="600px" /></a></p>

<p><a href="examples/randomization/pintori_1/index.html">See example code</a></p>

<p>Now we add colors.</p>

<p><a href="http://assets.runemadsen.com/randomization_simple-26569d6cadb7b5261a47420447529e01_large.png"><img src="http://assets.runemadsen.com/randomization_simple-26569d6cadb7b5261a47420447529e01_medium.png" srcset="http://assets.runemadsen.com/randomization_simple-26569d6cadb7b5261a47420447529e01_medium.png 800w, http://assets.runemadsen.com/randomization_simple-26569d6cadb7b5261a47420447529e01_large.png 1440w" sizes="600px" /></a></p>

<p><a href="examples/randomization/pintori_2/index.html">See example code</a></p>

<p>In the examples above, there are 2 problems:</p>

<ol>
  <li>The colors in the original work is not created by overlaying two triangles with different opacity 2. The shapes are going straight up in the air, and not rotating.</li>
</ol>

<p>This is solved in this (more complicated sketch) by using 3 different colors and 3 triangles, and calculating their placement using the <code class="highlighter-rouge">Rune.Polygon</code> and <code class="highlighter-rouge">centroid()</code>.</p>

<p><a href="http://assets.runemadsen.com/randomization-8e990f503b76f19ab059a6a1bd291da4_large.png"><img src="http://assets.runemadsen.com/randomization-8e990f503b76f19ab059a6a1bd291da4_medium.png" srcset="http://assets.runemadsen.com/randomization-8e990f503b76f19ab059a6a1bd291da4_medium.png 800w, http://assets.runemadsen.com/randomization-8e990f503b76f19ab059a6a1bd291da4_large.png 1440w" sizes="600px" /></a></p>

<p><a href="examples/randomization/pintori_3/index.html">See example code</a></p>

